org.openimaj.io

Interface ObjectReader<T,SOURCE>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - Type of object being read.
    SOURCE - The type of the source of data for the object being read
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    InputStreamObjectReader<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    OneSecondClipReader, VFSListDataset.FileObjectISReader

    public interface ObjectReader<T,SOURCE>
    Interface for classes capable of reading objects.

      • canRead

        boolean canRead(SOURCE source,
              String name)
        Returns true if the stream can be read, or false otherwise.

        This method is not normally called directly; rather, IOUtils.canRead(ObjectReader, Object, String) should be used instead.

        Parameters:
        source - the data source
        name - the name of the file behind the stream (can be null).
        Returns:
        true if this ObjectReader can read the stream; false otherwise.
        See Also:
        IOUtils.canRead(ObjectReader, Object, String)
